Definition.WordDefinition: Transcontinental \Trans*con`ti*nen"tal\, a. [Pref. trans- + continental.] Extending or going across a continent; as, a transcontinental railroad or journey. [1913 Webster]
transcontinental adj : spanning or crossing or on the farther side of a continent; "transcontinental railway"; "transcontinental travelers"; "a transcontinental city"
